---
import PolicyLayout from '../../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement | ISJ Jakarta"
  description="ISJ's Accessibility Statement sets out our commitment to making this website accessible to all users and how to report accessibility issues."
  policyName="Accessibility Statement"
  lastReviewed="April 2026"
  category="Operations and Governance"
  canonicalUrl="/policies/accessibility"
>

  <!-- Policy metadata -->
  <div class="policy-meta mb-14" style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--charcoal-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Author</span><span>Academic Director, April 2026</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Reviewed by</span><span>Board, April 2026</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Next review</span><span>Academic Director, April 2027</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Applies to</span><span>isj.id and international-school-jakarta.id</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-body" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: var(--font-body); color: var(--color-charcoal); line-height: 1.75;">

    <h2 id="commitment">Our Commitment</h2>
    <p>ISJ is committed to making its website accessible to as many people as possible, including those with visual, hearing, motor, or cognitive impairments. This statement applies to all pages published at isj.id.</p>

    <h2 id="standards">Accessibility Standard</h2>
    <p>ISJ aims to meet the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA. This means:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Text has sufficient colour contrast against its background</li>
      <li>All images include descriptive alt text</li>
      <li>The site can be navigated using a keyboard alone</li>
      <li>Page structure uses proper heading hierarchy</li>
      <li>Forms include descriptive labels</li>
      <li>Videos and audio content will include captions or transcripts where published</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="known-issues">Known Limitations</h2>
    <p>ISJ is aware that a full accessibility audit has not yet been completed. A formal audit is planned as part of the pre-launch quality assurance process. Any known issues identified during that audit will be listed here with target remediation dates.</p>

    <h2 id="reporting">Reporting an Issue</h2>
    <p>If you experience any accessibility barrier on this website, please contact <a href="mailto:admissions@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">admissions@isj.id</a> with a description of the issue and the page URL. ISJ will respond within five working days and aim to resolve confirmed issues promptly.</p>

    <h2 id="alternative">Alternative Formats</h2>
    <p>If you need information from this website in a different format — such as large print, plain text, or audio — contact <a href="mailto:admissions@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">admissions@isj.id</a> and ISJ will do its best to accommodate the request.</p>

    <h2 id="review">Review</h2>
    <p>This statement is reviewed annually and updated to reflect any changes to the website or the results of accessibility testing.</p>

  </div>

</PolicyLayout>
